{
    "sectionNumber": "3.4",
    "title": "Population by Mother Tongue",
    "type": "multi-block",
    "blocks": [
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "Nepal is a nation with multi-ethnic, multi-lingual, and multi-cultural characteristics. Linguistic diversity is also seen in this sub-metropolitan city. Out of the total population of 164,444 in the sub-metropolitan city, the highest 80,738 i.e. 49.10 percent were found to speak Awadhi language while 54,680 i.e. 33.25 percent spoke Nepali and 9,957 i.e. 6.05 percent spoke Urdu language. Article 32 of the Constitution has established the right to language and culture as a fundamental right and according to clause 5 of the right to education in Article 31, \"every Nepali community residing in Nepal shall have the right to receive education in their mother tongue and to open and operate schools and educational institutions for that purpose as provided for by law.\" There is a provision that the sub-metropolitan city can make special arrangements for students who want to study in their mother tongue. Detailed details according to mother tongue are mentioned in the table."
